<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1000,1453]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis box="[198,309,1348,1373]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</emphasis>
We have studied the 
<typeStatus box="[557,619,1348,1374]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">types</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[657,849,1348,1373]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
Photopsis 
<taxonomicName authority="Ashmead" authorityName="Ashmead" box="[779,849,1348,1373]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Photomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nanus">nanus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
Ashmead and 
<taxonomicName authority="Fox" authorityName="Fox" authorityYear="1758" box="[1023,1270,1348,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Mutilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acontius">
<emphasis box="[1023,1215,1348,1373]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Mutilla acontius</emphasis>
Fox
</taxonomicName>
, and we agree with Ferguson’s (
<number box="[362,425,1386,1412]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" value="1967.0">1967</number>
) synonymies. This species is very small, and, size wise, along with 
<taxonomicName box="[1259,1354,1387,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sphaeropthalma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="becki">
<emphasis box="[1259,1354,1387,1412]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. becki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is the smallest species on the dunes.
</paragraph>
